-- Spain's Applus says sets IPO price at 14.5 euros a share
-- By Paul Day
-- Thu May 08, 2014 01:18AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, May 8 (Reuters) - Spanish testing and inspection services company Applus <IPO-AST.MC> said early Thursday it had set the price for its Madrid stock market listing at 14.5 euros ($20.19) per share.

The market valuation of Applus, which is owned by U.S. private equity firm Carlyle <CG.O>, would be 1.9 billion euros based on the price.